
Write pseudocode for a function that checks if a string is a palindrome.

BEGIN

INPUT word

SET reversedword = reverse(word)

IF word EQUALS reversedword THEN

PRINT "yes, it is a palindrome"

ELSE

PRINT "no, it is not a palindrome"

END IF

END
Implement your solution in Python.

word = input("mum:") reversed_word = word[::-1] if word == reversed_word: print("yes, it is a palindrome") else: print("no,it is not a palindrome")

Test with examples like "racecar", "hello", and "A man a plan a canal Panama"


